Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 11:53:31 2026 -0400

    feat(conference)(conference-detail): URL brands + Hotel + Conference schema growth + defaults

    Branch 3 sub-commit 3.1. Grow the Conference document schema with the
    detail-page data the forked /YYYY pages hard-coded, modelling the optional
    fields as Option at the document layer so Branch 4's section-skip has a real
    Option.some/none discriminator (make-impossible-states-unrepresentable):

    - ExternalHttpsUrl: per-component XSS boundary (parses the URL; requires
      https:, rejects embedded credentials). Modelled on assetKeyFilter, NOT a
      substring/origin test.
    - GoogleMapsEmbedUrl: ExternalHttpsUrl + host === www.google.com AND
      pathname starts with /maps/embed. Host+path, NOT origin (origin excludes
      the path, would admit www.google.com/anything).
    - Hotel struct (id: ListItemId, name: Text, note?: Text) + DraftHotel.
    - Conference grows registrationUrl/scheduleUrl (ExternalHttpsUrl),
      mapEmbedUrl (GoogleMapsEmbedUrl) as OptionFromOptionalKey, and hotels as an
      id-keyed empty-able list.
    - Defaults: 2024 gets all (its real RegFox/schedule/map URLs + 5 hotels);
      2026 gets only registrationUrl (RegFox, the live channel); 2025 gets
      nothing optional (cancelled year).
    - schema.test.ts: URL-brand accept/reject matrices, incl. the origin-vs-path
      case GoogleMapsEmbedUrl must reject.

